<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1325,1598,1905]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,409,1598,1624]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Description</emphasis>
.—Male. Body length 
<quantity box="[690,767,1599,1625]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
; LFW 
<quantity box="[860,959,1599,1625]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" unit="mm" value="2.8">2.8 mm</quantity>
. Color: head and mesonotum black, except the pronotum dark castaneous, metanotum rufous castaneous, mandible and antenna castaneous, palpi, tegula and legs castaneous, wings hyaline, veins castaneous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[264,1325,1598,1905]" lastBlockId="4.[264,1323,284,1150]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="5" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,379,1718,1744]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[395,467,1719,1745]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 7. 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[264,368,1516,1540]" captionTargetBox="[316,1283,527,1481]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[305,1292,502,1509]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 7. 1 – 4 Apenesia membranaceus sp. nov. 1, head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 2 – 3, mandible, frontal view, 2 holotype; 3, paratype; 4, genitalia, ventral view; 5 – 7, Apenesia auricula sp. nov. 5, head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 6 mandible, frontal view; 7, genitalia, ventral view (Scale bars = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158459/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[450,467,1719,1745]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
): mandible with one apical tooth large, the others forming a cutting edge (
<figureCitation box="[273,345,1759,1785]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 7. 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[264,368,1516,1540]" captionTargetBox="[316,1283,527,1481]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[305,1292,502,1509]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 7. 1 – 4 Apenesia membranaceus sp. nov. 1, head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 2 – 3, mandible, frontal view, 2 holotype; 3, paratype; 4, genitalia, ventral view; 5 – 7, Apenesia auricula sp. nov. 5, head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 6 mandible, frontal view; 7, genitalia, ventral view (Scale bars = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158459/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Fig. 
<number box="[328,345,1759,1785]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
). Clypeus with angulate median lobe, median carina weak. First four antennal segment in a ratio of 
<number box="[470,505,1799,1825]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="28.0">28</number>
: 
<number box="[510,526,1799,1825]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="9.0">9</number>
: 
<number box="[530,563,1799,1825]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="14.0">14</number>
: 
<number box="[568,599,1799,1825]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="13.0">13</number>
, segment III 
<number box="[752,789,1799,1825]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="2.8">2.8</number>
X as long as broad, segment XI 
<number box="[1168,1205,1799,1825]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="2.7">2.7</number>
X as long asbroad. Eyes glabrous. Frons polished, with few punctures conspicuous and sparse. WH 1.0 X LH; WF 
<number box="[451,502,1879,1905]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="0.61">0.61</number>
X WH; WF 
<number box="[662,713,1879,1905]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1.23">1.23</number>
X HE; OOL 
<number box="[879,916,1879,1905]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" value="1.4">1.4</number>
X WOT; posterior ocellus distant from the crest of vertex 
<number box="[558,595,284,310]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1.5">1.5</number>
X 
<collectingCountry box="[635,702,284,310]" name="Iceland" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15671" box="[635,702,284,310]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15671" name="Agriculture and Agri-Food Canada" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">DAO</collectionCode>
</collectingCountry>
; frontal angle of ocellar triangle acute. Head nearly quadrate, but convergent behind; vertex slightly convex, corners broadly rounded. VOL 
<number box="[264,315,364,390]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="0.68">0.68</number>
X HE.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1323,284,1150]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,444,403,429]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Mesosoma</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[462,536,404,430]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 7. 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[264,368,1516,1540]" captionTargetBox="[316,1283,527,1481]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[305,1292,502,1509]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 7. 1 – 4 Apenesia membranaceus sp. nov. 1, head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 2 – 3, mandible, frontal view, 2 holotype; 3, paratype; 4, genitalia, ventral view; 5 – 7, Apenesia auricula sp. nov. 5, head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 6 mandible, frontal view; 7, genitalia, ventral view (Scale bars = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158459/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number box="[519,536,404,430]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
): thorax polished. Pronotal disc with anterior carina, and shallow posterior transverse depression. Notauli strongly defined, very thin anteriorly. Parapsidal furrows very weak and absent in the anterior third. Propodeal disc 
<number box="[1047,1098,484,510]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1.15">1.15</number>
X as wide as long, polished except the basal triangle, with median carina incomplete posteriorly, discal carinae only anteriorly defined; declivity with surface strigulate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1323,284,1150]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,442,603,629]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Metasoma</emphasis>
: polished and petiolate. Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[859,933,604,630]" captionStart="FIGURE 1 – 7. 1 – 4" captionStartId="2.[264,368,1516,1540]" captionTargetBox="[316,1283,527,1481]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[305,1292,502,1509]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1 – 7. 1 – 4 Apenesia membranaceus sp. nov. 1, head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 2 – 3, mandible, frontal view, 2 holotype; 3, paratype; 4, genitalia, ventral view; 5 – 7, Apenesia auricula sp. nov. 5, head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 6 mandible, frontal view; 7, genitalia, ventral view (Scale bars = 1 mm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/158459/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number box="[915,933,604,630]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
): paramere with apex wide, with an irregularly margined concavity, inner corners rounded and folded downwards, whole ventral surface concave; volsella with the ventral ramus of digitus with dilated base, apex narrow; aedeagus with two pairs of apical lobes, the lateral pair wide and with sharpened apex, the median pair slender and barely shorter than the lateral one.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
