<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1323,284,1150]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,414,1004,1030]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Remark</emphasis>
.—The genitalia of this species is very similar to those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kieffer, 1910" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1910" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paraensis">
<emphasis box="[1096,1243,1004,1029]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">A. paraensis</emphasis>
(Kieffer, 
<number box="[309,371,1044,1070]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1910.0">1910</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Evans, 1963" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1963" box="[392,683,1044,1070]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrata">
<emphasis box="[392,531,1044,1069]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">A. quadrata</emphasis>
Evans, 
<number box="[624,683,1044,1070]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1963.0">1963</number>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Evans, 1963" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1963" box="[738,1015,1044,1070]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laticeps">
<emphasis box="[738,861,1044,1069]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">A. laticeps</emphasis>
Evans, 
<number box="[954,1015,1044,1070]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1963.0">1963</number>
</taxonomicName>
, but the lateral pair of apical lobes of the aedeagus is different in being dome­shaped.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[312,1198,1124,1150]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="etymology">
